  "description" : "[h1]What does this mod do?[/h1]\nThis mod basically exists to smooth things out between Frackin and Project Redemption, including resolving some minor incompatibilities and offering some integration, in particular it:\n[list]\n[*]Allows for USCM remnant bunkers to spawn on a vast majority of FU's planets.\n[*]Adds Frackin stats to the Prismatic and Impervious sets, including their shields, making them into hyper tank sets with some elemental protections/resistances.\n[*]The Platinum set has been patched to have Frackin stats to it too, and can also be crafted as tier 4 equipment unlocked by Durasteel research.\n[*]The Heavy Peacekeeper armor set has also received FU stats as a balanced set.\n[*]Completely rebalances the Protector's set (including its recipe) into a tank exploration set brought in line with FU's tier 7 sets, coming with a damage buff to Protectorate themed weapons. It still features its built in techs.\n[*]All weapons from Project Redemption and its addons deal crit damage now and have their proper FU tags. As a bonus this includes the [url=https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=2791504358]Reprisal[/url] mod too.\n[*]All applicable items have crucible support. Now including a little extra for the Damaged and Protector's Handgun!\n[*]The lost and found merchant will now sell FU's starting pistol and protectorate shield.\n[*]The Damaged Handgun can now be crafted like the Broken Broadsword.\n[*]The fallen meteor microdungeons now can spawn on Dark Lava oceans while Impervium ore itself now spawns on the islands of both vanilla and dark Lava oceans.\n[*]Minor compatibility fixes relating to the Fossil Minigame, Ruin quest rewards, and Intro Mission.\n[*]Integration with the [url=https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=2003959183]Nitrogen Deep[/url] addon to FU\n[*]FU stats for the Widefire mech arm\n[*]Other small integrations.\n[/list]\n\n[h2]Q and A:[/h2]\n[h2]why does the USCM remnant bunker look so much like the cultist lair in FU?[/h2]\nthe cultist lair dungeon is a unused vanilla one actually, don't believe me? try doing \"/placedungeon cultistlair\" without the quotes in admin mode (in a vanilla copy of the game)\nthe USCM remnant bunker is just based off of that vanilla dungeon\n\n[h2]do you have a discord server for project redemption and your other mods?[/h2]\nyup! you can access it [url=https://discord.gg/PFMNxFu]here[/url]\n\nCredits:\nHuge thanks to Khe for making the statuseffect/lua behind the protector's armor set bonus and for helping me keep the set balanced within FU confines, Lack of Creativity for helping me test this mod and make the screenshots for it, Anom for the mod icon, and lastly Chucklefish for making this wonderful game!",
